notesStmt.note: Based on the handwriting and the material on the back of the leaf, this manuscript was likely written between 1850 and 1855, when Whitman was composing his first edition of Leaves of Grass. The lines do not have any known relation to Whitman's published poetry.

But I am sure it will be generous enough,

I have never yet seen the sign of a niggard
in any thing but undeveloped man.—
